Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

Thanks Zhi Yan: we need this patch to fix tempest!

Before this patch I was getting:
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: ======================================================================
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: FAIL: setUpClass (tempest.api.image.v1.test_images.ListImagesTest)
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: setUpClass (tempest.api.image.v1.test_images.ListImagesTest)
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: ----------------------------------------------------------------------
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: _StringException: Traceback (most recent call last):
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:   File "tempest/api/image/v1/test_images.py", line 116, in setUpClass
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:     img1 = cls._create_remote_image('one', 'bare', 'raw')
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:   File "tempest/api/image/v1/test_images.py", line 150, in _create_remote_image
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:     location=location)
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:   File "tempest/api/image/base.py", line 78, in create_image
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:     disk_format, **kwargs)
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:   File "tempest/services/image/v1/json/image_client.py", line 155, in create_image
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:     resp, body = self.post('v1/images', None, headers)
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:   File "tempest/common/rest_client.py", line 199, in post
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:     return self.request('POST', url, headers, body)
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:   File "tempest/common/rest_client.py", line 374, in request
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:     resp, resp_body)
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:   File "tempest/common/rest_client.py", line 423, in _error_checker
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out:     raise exceptions.BadRequest(resp_body)
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: BadRequest: Bad request
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: Details: 400 Bad Request
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: 
2014-03-14 12:12:15 | [10.36.1.18] out: External sourcing not supported for store http://example.com/someimage_New Remote Image one.iso

because http was not in the store_scheme.

I have tested with this patch. It fixes tempest.

Patch Set 1:

BTW: this is not specific to swift.
You will get this behavior as soon as your config is
default_store = something different than file/http
known_store = something different than file/http

Patch Set 1: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

I think this might be missing the boat a little bit. What we want to do, IIUC is the following

If the config does not specify anything, we should keep the behavior from before, where we enable filesystem and http properly, but we also turn on and warn about all the old stores.

If the config specifies a list of stores, we should *only* enable those stores.

I'm probably willing to just let this patch in as is, however, to unbreak tempest for the time being. We can make it work the "right" way next week when we have a bit more time to discuss.

Patch Set 1:

Hi markwash, I'd like to try to answer you concerns here, and seems we have some mis-communications:

>>> If the config does not specify anything, we should keep the behavior from before, where we enable filesystem and http properly, but we also turn on and warn about all the old stores.

Right, current change followed the behaviour on what we did in "Provide an upgrade period for enabling stores" (#79935) change, form end user's perspective they could receive the same warning logic.

>>> If the config specifies a list of stores, we should *only* enable those stores.

IIUC, this is the finial target for glance in next release but this cycle because we now meet https://bugs.launchpad.net/glance/+bug/1290969 issue in upgrade scenario.

Actually this fix just resolved the issue which we made in "Provide an upgrade period for enabling stores" (#79935) change, and the all things what I did in this patch just unblock the upgrade scenario issue. I agreed the finial status of the code should be https://review.openstack.org/#/c/59150/12 , it is the "right" way for glance future I think so.
